'''Nigel Starmer-Smith''' is a [[British people|British]] [[rugby union]] journalist and commentator.

He played [[scrum half]] for [[Oxford University]], [[Harlequin F.C.|Harlequins]] and [[England national rugby union team|England]]. He has edited [[Rugby World]] magazine and for 15 years introduced [[Rugby Special]] for the [[BBC]]. He has also commentated on Olympic hockey for the BBC but had to make way for Barry Davies for the 1988 Olympic Final.


In the late 1960s he taught [[Geography]] at [[Epsom College]]

During the [[2003 Rugby World Cup|2003 World Cup]] in [[Australia]], Starmer-Smith commentated for [[ITV Sport]]'s coverage.

